investigation.title: Mouse muscle LC-MSMS upon weightlessness
investigation.description: Upon weightlessness and microgravity, deleterious effects on the neurosensory and neurovestibular systems, haematological changes, and deconditioning of musculoskeletal, cardiovascular and cardiopulmonary functions have been reported. In particular, loss of muscle mass and strength are triggered by weightlessness in humans during space flights, that is similarly observed as a result of physical inactivity conditions and aging on Earth.

project.funding: This work was supported by the French Space Agency, CNRS and Strasbourg University (H2E project), French Proteomic Infrastructure (ProFI; ANR-10-INSB-08-03), and the European Space Agency PRODEX programme with Enterprise Ireland. We thank Dr. B. Shenkman from the Institute for Biomedical Problems of the Russian Academy of Sciences (Moscow, Russia).

publications.title: Proteome-wide Adaptations of Mouse Skeletal Muscles during a Full Month in Space.
